Task: Add colors to the prompt

To add colors to the shell prompt use the following export command syntax:
'\e[x;ym $PS1 \e[m'
Where,

\e[ : Start color scheme.
x;y : Color pair to use (x;y)
$PS1 : Your shell prompt variable.
\e[m : Stop color scheme.


38;5;23m

# light blue
"\e[1;34m   \e[m"

# green 
"\e[0;32m   \e[m"

# cyan
"\e[0;36m   \e[m"